comments.body:
@darrell I'm not sure if you can catch the fact that FasterCSV can be installed but still be incompatible with Ruby 1.9.
I saw this kind of RUBY_VERSION test all over ActiveRecord or ActiveSupport source code to behave differently depending of the Ruby version and not the possible raised exceptions.
In this case it's the opposite of the duck-typing principle but I think it's a good way to do it.

